# Data Schemas

Reference for data interfaces and file locations. Use when creating or extending data files.

## profile.ts

**Location:** `src/data/profile.ts`

**Interfaces:**

```typescript
interface Highlight {
  number: string;
  label: string;
}

interface SkillCategory {
  title: string;
  icon: string;
  skills: string[];
  primary?: string[];
}

interface SocialLink {
  name: string;
  url: string;
  icon: string;
  ariaLabel: string;
}

interface Language {
  flag: string;
  name: string;
  level: string;
  native?: boolean;
}
```

**Export:** `profile` with: name, title, subtitle, availability, profileImage, email, location, resumeUrl, bio (intro, experience, passion), highlights, skills, socialLinks, footerSocialLinks, trustBadges, languages

## experiences.ts

**Location:** `src/data/experiences.ts`

**Interface:**

```typescript
interface Experience {
  position: string;
  work_mode: string;
  company: string;
  company_link: string;
  client: string;
  client_link: string;
  dates: string;
  present: boolean;
  description: string;  // HTML string, e.g. <ul><li>...</li></ul>
  disciplines: string;
  company_logo?: string;  // filename in public/images/companies/
  client_logo?: string;   // filename in public/images/companies/
}
```

**Export:** `experiences: Experience[]`

**Company logos:** Place WebP files in `public/images/companies/`. Convert via `tools/png_to_webp.py` (copy script to folder containing PNGs, then run).

